\[
3x - 2x - 9 = 2x - 2x + 74
\]

This simplifies to:

\[
x - 9 = 74
\]

Next, we add 9 to both sides to isolate \(x\):

\[
x - 9 + 9 = 74 + 9
\]

This simplifies to:

\[
x = 83
\]

