\]

6. **Compare with the original equation \(\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ \tan x^\circ = \tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ + \tan x^\circ\):**

We see that the right-hand side of the equation matches when \(x = 46^\circ\).

Therefore, the value of \(x\) that satisfies the given equation is \(46^\circ\).

