\[ f(-x) = -f(x) \]

So,
\[ g(f(-x)) = g(-f(x)) = g(f(x)) \]

Thus, \( g(f(x)) \) remains \( g(f(x)) \) when we evaluate at \( -x \).

Next, moving outward:
\[ f(g(f(-x))) = f(g(f(x))) \]

Our next evaluation involves \( g \)'s evenness:
