\[
g(-x) = g(x) \implies g(f(-g(x))) = g(f(g(x)))
\]

Since \( f(x) \) is odd:
\[
f(-u) = -f(u)
\]

Thus:
\[
f(f(g(f(-g(x))))) = f(f(g(f(g(x)))))
\]

Therefore, the function \( f(f(g(f(g(x))))) \) maps \( -x \) to the same value it maps \( x \) to, indicating it is an even function. Thus, \( f(f(g(f(g(x))))) \) is even.",1.5,Qwen/Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-Turbo,117,3281,,stop,og1CsEP-4YNCb4-9efb036a5a0a243a,
