   - Next, consider \( g(f(g(f(x)))) \). Since \( f(g(f(x))) \) is even, \( g(f(g(f(-x)))) = g(f(g(f(x)))) \). So, \( g(f(g(f(x)))) \) is even.
   - Finally, consider \( f(f(g(f(g(f(x)))))) \). Since \( g(f(g(f(x)))) \) is even, \( f(f(g(f(g(f(-x)))))) = f(f(g(f(g(f(x)))))) \). So, \( f(f(g(f(g(f(x)))))) \) is even.

3. **Conclusion:**
   - The function \( f(f(g(f(g(f(x)))))) \) is even because each step in the composition preserves the evenness of the function.

