1. **Base Case:**
   \[
   f(i, j) = \text{mod}_5(j + 1) \quad \text{if } i = 0 \text{ and } 0 \le j \le 4.
   \]
   This means for \( i = 0 \), the function simply returns the remainder when \( j + 1 \) is divided by 5.

2. **Recursive Cases:**
