\[ \text{Distance} = \frac{|Ax_1 + By_1 + C|}{\sqrt{A^2 + B^2}} \]

For line \(CD\):
\[ c = 0, d = 140/\sqrt{2} \]
\[ y = -\frac{c}{d}x + c \]
\[ y = -\frac{c}{140/\sqrt{2}}x + c \]
\[ y = -\frac{c\sqrt{2}}{140}x + c \]

The distance is:
\[ \text{Distance} = \frac{|0 - 10\sqrt{29} + c|}{\sqrt{(c\sqrt{2}/140)^2 + 1}} \]

